criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Inactive carrier status and chronic hepatitis B (CHB) patients with anti-viral therapy
             (interferon and nucleoside analogues) reaching HBsAg < 100 IU/ml.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  coinfection with other viruses including HCV, HDV, and HIV;

          -  syphilis antibody positive;

          -  co-exist other liver diseases including alcoholic liver disease, metabolic liver
             disease, fatty liver, drug induce liver injury, and autoimmune liver disease;

          -  complication of cirrhosis or liver cancer.
